    <summary>CyberBrick Apps are the official tools for Bambu Lab’s CyberBrick ecosystem. The desktop app provides a streamlined environment to create, edit, and publish projects and to prepare/flash configurations to Core boards. The mobile apps (iOS/Android) add Bluetooth connectivity, on-the-go project import, and quick adjustments.</summary>

    <description>CyberBrick Apps connect printable models, electronics, and coding into one end-to-end workflow—from downloading a project on MakerWorld to flashing it onto CyberBrick Core boards.

### Features
- **Desktop App:** Full editing of project/device configurations, spacious UI for efficient work; smooth handoff to your CAD and (for printed parts) Bambu Studio workflows.
- **Mobile Apps (iOS/Android):** Browse community projects, preview control layouts and assembly notes, connect to CyberBrick microcontrollers via **Bluetooth**, wirelessly deploy projects, and tweak parameters live.
- **Device Management:** Support for **MPY project flashing** and **firmware updates** (subject to version/release notes).

### What this package does
- Installs the **CyberBrick Desktop App for Windows** using the official installer.
- Suitable for unattended/automated deployments with Chocolatey.

### Compatibility / requirements
- **Windows 10/11** (per upstream support).
- Administrator privileges may be required.
- Note: **Mobile apps** for iOS/Android are obtained separately from their respective app stores.

### Post-install verification
- Launch “CyberBrick”, import a sample project from MakerWorld, pair a device via Bluetooth, and validate a configuration/preview.

